HEADWORD: Plack
<hw>Plack</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>plaque</ets> a
plate of metal. Cf. <er>Plaque</er>.]</ety> <def>A small copper coin
formerly current in Scotland, worth less than a cent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With not a <qex>plack</qex> in the pocket of the poet.</q>
<rj><qau>Prof. Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placket</ent>⟦br⟧
